videoSnippet.title: Peter Svidler Became an 8-time Russian Champion & re-entered the World Top 10!
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Played in the State Museum of the Political History of Russia, St. Petersburg, Russia 3-14 December 2017 (11 rounds).

The time control is 90 minutes for 40 moves then 30 minutes to the end of the game, with a 30-second increment from move 1. No draw offers are allowed before move 40. A tie for first place is split by two 15+10 rapid games and, if the score is still tied, a 5 vs. 4 Armageddon game, where Black wins if the game ends in a draw.

Peter Svidler vs Nikita Vitiugov
Russian Superfinals 2017. Tiebreaks
12. 14. 2017.

1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nf3 f5 4. d4 e4 5. d5 Nce7 6. Nd4 d6 7. f3 Ng6 8. fxe4 f4 9. g3 fxg3 10. hxg3 Nf6 11. Bh3 Ng4 12. Ne6 Bxe6 13. dxe6 N4e5 14. Bf5 c6 15. Be3 Qc7 16. Qb3 Ne7 17. O-O-O b6 18. Bf4
